rComments: Prof was very good at demonstrating how seemingly difficult concepts can be solvable using rudimentary concepts. This is the trick to tackling most midterm question. Just make sure you do enough practice questions to get the hang of it. The course moves very fast so make sure you absolutely don't fall behind.

Best engineering prof I've ever had - delivers the material with enthusiasm, links it to current research, and appears to care about his students' success a great deal. Only 9AM lecture slot I've ever looked forward to
provides intuitive explanations to complicated concepts, inspirational lecturer, if you truly understands what he taught in lecture, the tests will be easy

He's managed to make one of the most interesting courses in first year engsci into a living hell for students. Explains topics clearly during lecture, but then side swipes you with a horrendously difficult termtest/exam. Believes that a 68 is a great average in an Engsci course... no other prof shares that opinion

He is one of the best lecturers I have ever had. He explains everything very clearly, albeit fast occasionally, but if you pay attention you'll most likely learn almost everything from the lectures, as he actively tries to make it so that you can learn all of the concepts in class. Lastly, the more you participate, the more you can get from him.

failed at his promise of getting everyone to understand. course average was a C+. had great lectures at the beginning, then sped up and went waaay too fast. tests and exams were unreasonably hard and long.

Awesome prof. Makes sure everyone understands, even changed the semester's schedule to make sure everyone understands! His amazing enthusiasm makes everything very interesting. Tests are tough though.
He is an amazing prof, very knowledgeable. He really  cares for his students and is willing to explain anything to you so don't be shy to ask. Make sure to attend every lecture!
He is an amazing lecturer with pretty good notes, but his tests are very difficult. Expects a lot from his students.
Amazing prof. Knows his stuff, and teaches it incredibly well. Genuinely wants students to learn and cares how they do in his class.
Best Prof Ever! He is super clear, however his tests are tough.
One of THE BEST prof i have had in 4 years ... his explanations are AWESOME ... I wouldnt take this course with anyone except him ... SIMPLY THE BEST!!!

One of the best profs I've EVER had. He's a great teacher. His notes aren't the best, but they will do. His explanations are INCREDIBLE though. If you take this class, make sure it is with him. Prior to this class, I was soooo confused about transistors and everything, he   changed that completely!!! GREAT PROF!!!

Great prof, has a real passion for the material. Will try and get you to understand what's going on as much as possible. Sadly, his teaching methods leave you thinking you know everything, then screw up the exam. His exams are tough, but he teaches well so he expects a lot from students. GO TO CLASS. Not a hard course if you spend a littletimeonit.
Quote from the proffessor:" The best way to teach is not to teach at all." HONESTLY. HE SAID THAT!!! AND HE ACTUALLY DOESN'T TEACH!!! I DIDN"T LEARN ANYTHING FROM HIM.

His lectures are probably  the best in the ECE dept.He knows his material and explains it very well (you will definetly not loose your attention in his class) ... It is true that his personality socks, but as a student I don't care.
No Comments
he has a rotten personality; too bad since he seems like he knows his stuff
Agree with previous comment
